---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About daggerobelus">
  <section class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif leading-tight mb-8">About</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg text-ink/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p>
          <strong>Daggerobelus</strong> takes its name from typographical symbols—the dagger (†) and obelus (÷)—marks traditionally used by scribes and editors to annotate texts, flag questionable passages, or indicate critical apparatus.
        </p>

        <p>
          This site features in-depth explorations of interesting topics, powered by NLP, data analysis, and interactive visualizations. Each project combines rigorous research methodology with modern computational tools to uncover patterns and tell stories hidden in historical sources.
        </p>

        <p>
          Projects may incorporate entity extraction and relationship mapping, network analysis and graph visualizations, statistical modeling, and interactive data explorations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
